        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> May&#47;49</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><persName>Mr Joseph Lyons</persName> the<lb/> bearer of this&#44; intends taking up his residence<lb/> in your city&#44; and when I tell you that<lb/> he is a gentleman who has obtained the<lb/> respectful consideration of all who have<lb/> known him during his stay in <placeName>Montreal</placeName>&#8212;<lb/>&#8212;that he has been a warm supporter of<lb/> our Synagogue&#44; and taken an active part<lb/> as Committeeman in conducting the affairs of<lb/> our Philanthropic Society&#8212;and thus he is<lb/> one for whom I entertain very warm sentiments<lb/> of friendship and esteem&#44; I am sure I need<lb/> add nothing to induce you to do your best<lb/> to render his stay in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> as<lb/> pleasant and profitable as you possibly can<lb/> make it. I doubt not but that you<lb/> will be able to inform him of one or two</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>things that may be of service to him</p>
			<p>Any attention shown him will be duly<lb/> appreciated by Yours very faithfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p>Favor <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p><persName>J Lyons Esqr</persName></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
